column216: I could guess whether or not the player would play the game depending on what I had highlighted and what was possible versus whether or not their possibilites were above the guaranteed payoff.  By guessing whether or not they would play  I could figure out my chances for winning if they did play.
Tried to predict what the other players would do..if the choices seemed to good to be true  the majority of the time they were and it was safer to choose the safe amount.

lets say i am player one  i would first assume player two has only once choice  which is state A  if payoff of state A for player two is less than the sure payoff  then i would compare my state B with the sure payoff  if my state B payoff is higher  i choose to play the game  if its lower  i will not play the game.

I basicaly didn't play when I knew when my sure payoff was higher than what i had and when i figured that the other person wasn't going to play.  But i did play when my surepayoff was higher  no matter what the other person had. When my surepayoff was lower but i had the gamble of getting something higher i only gambled when what i was going to lose was minimal (i.e. 5 points usually).
Don't play if the choices seemed potentially lower than the sure payoff
one strategy was that If my highlighted box had a greater amount than the Sure Payoff  i would  play the game hoping that my partner would do the same.

I would try to guess wether the other player would play the game or not and base my decision on the that.  So sometimes the decision of full proff.  For example if player 1 was sure that it was C and C was lower than the sure payoff then I would definetly choose to play the game because I would know that if it was C then player 1 would choose not to play the game.

if the show up fee was higher than the 1 box highlighted  always played the game.   i calculated the chance that an opponent would play or not play to decide if it was risking getting a smaller amount than the sure     pay off.
Tried to see guage the likelihood of the states
oppertunity cost  and i attempted to predict what the other player would pick based upon their set of numbers and the sure payoff.
